N = -\mathbf{i}\cdot \left(-\dfrac{x}{za^2}\right) - \mathbf{j}\cdot \left(-\dfrac{y}{za^2}\right) + \mathbf{k} = \left(\dfrac{x}{za^2}, \dfrac{y}{za^2}, 1\right)
||N|| = \sqrt{\dfrac{x^2}{a^4z^2} + \dfrac{y^2}{a^4z^2} + 1} = \dfrac{1}{za^2}\cdot \sqrt{x^2 + y^2 + a^4z^2} = \dfrac{1}{za^2}\cdot \sqrt{a^2(1-z^2) + a^4z^2} = \dfrac{a}{za^2}\cdot \sqrt{1+(a^2-1)z^2} = \dfrac{\sqrt{1+(a^2-1)z^2}}{az}
